cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and language models. The use of deep bidirectional transformer language models for stance detection also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves transfer learning, which is a common technique in the field of machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
